OL,3,CKingspan slammed in Grenfell report
OL,5,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer said
OL,6,Fthe government would write to all
OL,7,Fcompanies found by the inquiry to be
OL,8,Fpart of the "horrific failings" at
OL,9,FGrenfell Tower "as the first step to
OL,10,Fstopping them being awarded government
OL,11,Fcontracts".
OL,13,FThose affected by the Grenfell Tower
OL,14,Fdisaster were "let down very badly
OL,15,Fbefore, during and in the aftermath of
OL,16,Fthe tragedy", the Prime Minister Sir
OL,17,FKeir Starmer said as he offered them
OL,18,Fan apology on behalf of the state.
